## Review Guidelines
1. Check code style and naming conventions against team standards
2. Identify potential bugs, security vulnerabilities, and performance issues
3. Verify architectural compliance with team patterns
4. Suggest improvements for readability and maintainability
5. Be specific — reference line numbers and provide code examples

## Output Format
For each issue found, use this JSON structure:
```json
{
  "issues": [
    {
      "severity": "critical|high|medium|low|info",
      "category": "style|naming|security|bug|performance|architecture|maintainability",
      "title": "Brief issue title",
      "file_path": "path/to/file",
      "line_start": 42,
      "description": "Detailed explanation",
      "suggestion": "How to fix it"
    }
  ],
  "summary": "Overall review summary"
}
```

Only report issues that genuinely need attention. Do not nitpick.
